The paper deals with multiple-antenna systems and proposes low complexity methods for integer-forcing receivers in a block fading scenario. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions interference cancellation, which is a common technique in Signal Processing (cs.SP) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of root LDPC codes, which are commonly used in Coding Theory (cs.IT) and Computer Communications (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with multiple access channels, which is a topic in Multimedia (cs.MM).
